         <abstract>

            <p>There are documents which only include the formula <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወሀብኩ፡</foreign>,
                but do not specify the type of the land ownership, even if they contain a precise register of the locations
              involved (e.g., Liber axumae nos. 77, 80, EDL no. 32). Sometimes
                we can only assume that the document is about gwǝlt since the term is not clearly mentioned
                (<ref corresp="BLorient481" type="mss">BritLib Or. 481</ref>, f. 92r, 124v; seems to be very frequent in the “copies” of the charters).</p>
         </abstract>
